snippet: Anne W. Patterson, a press-shy career diplomat who has been American ambassador to Cairo since 2011, has suddenly found herself a target in a dangerous political upheaval.
abstract: Anne W Patterson, press-shy career diplomat who has been American ambassador to Cairo since 2011, suddenly finds herself a target in country's dangerous political upheaval; angry young Egyptians view Patterson as representative of America's meddlesome role in their country's affairs.

byline.contributor: Sarah Mousa contributed reporting from Cairo, and Thom Shanker from Washington.

lead_paragraph: Anne W. Patterson, a press-shy career diplomat who has been American ambassador to Cairo since 2011, has suddenly found herself a target in a dangerous political upheaval.
